# Always link the plan at the end

Whenever you **create**, **update**, or **execute** a plan, end your response
with a clickable markdown link to the plan file(s) so the user can open them in
one click.

- Link `PLAN.md` (and `RESEARCH.md` / any sibling doc you touched) by its path.
- Put the link(s) on the **last line(s)** of the response, under a short label.
- If multiple plan files were created/changed, link each one.
- Applies to plan folders under `plans/NNN-name/` and any ad-hoc plan file.

Example ending:

> Plan: [plans/008.96-file-image-display/PLAN.md](plans/008.96-file-image-display/PLAN.md)
> Research: [plans/008.96-file-image-display/RESEARCH.md](plans/008.96-file-image-display/RESEARCH.md)
